Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.56,0:00:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That peddler said \Nit was just behind that mountain pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.48,0:00:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,More like three mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.07,0:00:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro's picked up \Na weird habit too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.41,0:00:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo, a horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.70,0:00:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we should've gotten one \Nif it was going to be this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.37,0:00:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not walking any further \Neven if that blacksmith isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.96,0:00:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I need this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.97,0:00:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If not here, we walk more.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.05,0:00:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, I didn't really mean that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.06,0:01:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.47,0:01:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he said the swordmaker's name \Nwas Munetsuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.60,0:01:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.33,0:01:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Betrayed this world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.54,0:01:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And it simmers within
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.75,0:01:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Rupturing my innards
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.97,0:01:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Swelling a reddish black
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.10,0:01:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the sun burnt skin ruptures
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.81,0:01:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a light  \N in the depths of the seething darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.65,0:01:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirming each other's voices  \N in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.82,0:02:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As if to stroke with wet fingertips
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.99,0:02:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to touch you one day
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.83,0:02:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a light  \N in the depths of the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.01,0:02:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirming each other's voices  \N in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.18,0:02:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As if to stroke with wet fingertips
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.39,0:02:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to touch you one day
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.03,0:02:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,#19 The story of the Amanojaku
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.20,0:02:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Munetsuna? He lives on the outskirts \Nof the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.45,0:02:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-Really? \N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.46,0:02:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're not going to ask him \Nto forge a sword, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.54,0:02:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's a really skilled craftsman, \Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.51,0:03:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, he's nothing of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.30,0:03:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's not what the peddler told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.43,0:03:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He forged that hatchet for me, \Nbut I'm not impressed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And his daughter, Okowa, is really ugly \Nand has a bad personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.90,0:03:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never liked them too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.74,0:03:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.62,0:03:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming. Here to complain \Nabout my papa again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.87,0:03:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.92,0:03:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.96,0:03:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this Munetsuna's place?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.55,0:03:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's my papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.01,0:03:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're Okowa?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.18,0:03:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.64,0:03:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We were traveling and heard that \Nyour papa forged great swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.35,0:03:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, a customer. Yeah, my papa's \Nthe best swordmaker in the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.94,0:03:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.73,0:03:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.32,0:04:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez. The people here \Nalways lie like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.28,0:04:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But they still come to Papa for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.20,0:04:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's really good?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.33,0:04:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.62,0:04:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then can he reforge these for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.37,0:04:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, they've really been through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.00,0:04:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro, I told you not to do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.35,0:04:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You just can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.77,0:04:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-Why? \N-Because I say so!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.77,0:04:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.74,0:04:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He might get mad if we disturb him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.49,0:04:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.33,0:04:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,First impressions are really important, \Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.67,0:04:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Have your sword out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.84,0:05:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at that funny thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.68,0:05:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa, you have customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.01,0:05:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants you to reforge some swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.68,0:05:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably wants to marry me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.27,0:05:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-What are you doing! \N-Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.11,0:05:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa, don't get angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.15,0:05:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,First impressions are important, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Those swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.99,0:05:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you killed with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.16,0:05:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are we doing this? \NWe've never purified a sword before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.79,0:05:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.52,0:05:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Bishamon, the guardian god \Nlooks over this temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.60,0:05:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa and everyone else at the village \Npray to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.52,0:06:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That Hyottoko is another god. \NOne of forging.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.03,0:06:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a god? It has a funny face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.20,0:06:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it's blowing on the embers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.99,0:06:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Blowing on embers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.58,0:06:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been passed down for generations \Nin our family to keep away misfortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.33,0:06:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hyottoko god, blowing on embers huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.58,0:06:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody blows on embers like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.72,0:06:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.26,0:06:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.81,0:06:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Put the swords there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.60,0:06:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.11,0:06:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck are you doing, bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.78,0:06:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-What...? \N-Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.33,0:06:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the time to fool around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.51,0:07:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"INN"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pooped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.35,0:07:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That Munetsuna guy said he'd bring \Nthe swords here when they're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.73,0:07:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The swords will come here...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.98,0:07:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So let's get some rest till then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.94,0:07:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not going to cost us as much \Nas I thought, so we can just relax here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.24,0:07:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.79,0:07:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be really tired. I thought I heard \Nyou say you didn't need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.17,0:07:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't need them...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.00,0:07:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck do you mean? \NYou need them to get your body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.51,0:07:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hyaku, Dororo. It's me, Okowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:07:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.06,0:08:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hyaku?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.10,0:08:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you might be hungry, \Nso I made this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.15,0:08:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, I was getting hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, looks yummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.86,0:08:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Dororo. The master of the house \Ngets to eat first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.08,0:08:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Master? And who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.96,0:08:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, bro and I are on \Na really important journey right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.04,0:08:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the swords are done, we're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.59,0:08:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm prepared to go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.05,0:08:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you crazy? It's not some joyride. \NI'm the only one who can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.51,0:08:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I'm the daughter of \Nthe land's best swordmaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.39,0:08:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dang it, you tell her bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.94,0:08:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That you can't be with Okowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.23,0:08:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be with Okowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.90,0:08:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hyaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.49,0:08:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you shouldn't joke around like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.87,0:08:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Not joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.99,0:09:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-But the journey... \N-I quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.20,0:09:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rest of your body?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.29,0:09:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't want it. I'm fine like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.58,0:09:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Body?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.58,0:09:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-Stop joking already, I mean it. \N-Not joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.21,0:09:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.42,0:09:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have to be together anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.27,0:09:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hyaku, I don't mind, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.69,0:09:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo can stay with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.94,0:09:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Say that again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.36,0:09:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need Dororo with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.99,0:09:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, have it your way. I hate you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.28,0:09:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You big ole dummy idiot jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.99,0:09:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen here. I'm really glad that \Nyou and Okowa are getting together!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.63,0:09:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-What did I just...? \N-Oh, Dororo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.46,0:09:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You two were meant for each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.88,0:09:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, I'm so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.30,0:10:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep talking. I really think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.26,0:10:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh, Dororo. \N-Mumble, grumble, rumble...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.89,0:10:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Mr. Hyaku's sushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.36,0:10:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Little Dororo, crying for us like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.32,0:10:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo looked happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.95,0:10:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro, you big ole jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.91,0:10:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care about you anymore. I mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.60,0:10:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My condolences. What a great tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it truly is. \NOnly bad things to come now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.82,0:10:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:11:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I told the villagers that I was going \Nto marry you, and now look at all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.41,0:11:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okowa, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.41,0:11:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They say wedding attire makes a girl glow. \NI'll make one to make you look shabby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.29,0:11:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can count on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.25,0:11:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay then. \NThey're always like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.80,0:11:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for you, Okowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.67,0:11:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd been hoping you'd hurry up \Nand get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.09,0:11:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope you have a good wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.01,0:11:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.14,0:11:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He's honest for once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.31,0:11:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a wedding?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.52,0:11:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you and I \Nare going to be husband and wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.15,0:11:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Husband and wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.40,0:11:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the earlier the better,  \N so I set it for tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.70,0:11:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's way too fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.66,0:11:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.13,0:11:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.96,0:12:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wedding? Hah! I congratulate you \Nfrom the bottom of my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.93,0:12:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen here. \NNo matter what anyone might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.23,0:12:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you're gonna be happy together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.56,0:12:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We sure will be, Dororo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.36,0:12:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh dang it, what's happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.99,0:12:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't eat that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.99,0:12:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.91,0:12:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I will become Okowa's husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo looked happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck, bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.98,0:12:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All head over heels for Okowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.06,0:12:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You like her so much, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.99,0:13:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine then. You have it your way,  \N and I'll have it mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.70,0:13:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.79,0:13:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,My, how ugly you look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.41,0:13:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a plain girl. \NYou put this lovely kimono to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.13,0:13:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hyaku, you're not supposed to see yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.26,0:13:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my. How ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.55,0:13:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The swords will come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.48,0:13:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't need the swords, \NI'll throw them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.66,0:13:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I really am going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.59,0:14:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.55,0:14:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-Don't scare me like that. \N-Who's scaring who?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.73,0:14:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bro's new sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.19,0:14:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not done yet. \NI've just been to purify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.69,0:14:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you going to do with that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.57,0:14:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why you wanted \Nto throw them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.04,0:14:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro suddenly lost interest in the journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.00,0:14:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say things I don't mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.04,0:14:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.71,0:14:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro doesn't understand how I feel at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.01,0:14:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He's helped me out a whole bunch \Never since we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd made up my mind to help him \Nget through rough times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.35,0:15:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I swore that I would.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.48,0:15:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.31,0:15:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How can he quit the journey now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.53,0:15:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I came for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.49,0:15:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You just came for me a few days ago. \NYou jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.83,0:15:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I just fall asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.18,0:15:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-Don't bother me. \N-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.35,0:15:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to Okowa's wedding?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.06,0:15:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is more important to a swordmaker \Nthan making swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.07,0:15:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okowa understands.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.82,0:15:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You really like swords, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.65,0:15:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You hate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.24,0:15:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate samurai.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.99,0:15:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't like swords made for killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.58,0:16:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate people killing people, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.46,0:16:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My ideal is to make a sword \Nthat makes fighting cease.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.80,0:16:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A sword that makes the enemy see \Nthat they're no match and give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.01,0:16:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.14,0:16:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be easy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.68,0:16:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I might not live to see it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.52,0:16:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I just know I shouldn't use my powers \Nfor the wrong cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.78,0:16:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wrong. I have to stay by bro's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.07,0:16:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really mean that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.37,0:16:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.37,0:16:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? I've been saying \Nwhat I really mean, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.67,0:16:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Why am I okay when I'm here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.00,0:16:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, since when have I \Nbeen talking in opposites?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.26,0:16:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro... What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.14,0:17:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Since when has he been weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.44,0:17:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.61,0:17:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,-Come on, we have to go to the temple. \N-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.15,0:17:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,To get married, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.12,0:17:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers will hold a celebration \Nfor us afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.83,0:17:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The swords will come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.75,0:17:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They can come \Nwhen we get back from the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.83,0:17:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The swords will come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.14,0:17:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it you that did all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.85,0:17:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.57,0:17:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-Dororo? \N-Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.78,0:18:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that creature!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.58,0:18:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That ghoul is probably what made us \Nact weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.83,0:18:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.84,0:18:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.51,0:18:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not me. Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.85,0:18:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hyaku, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.39,0:18:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.56,0:18:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.60,0:18:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to kill Dororo, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.49,0:18:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.04,0:18:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.84,0:18:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.59,0:18:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I doubted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.14,0:19:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd have thought it was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was all this ghoul's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.11,0:19:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Legend has it there was once an Amanojaku \Nthat worked mischief in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.49,0:19:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was confined here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we really were protected \Nby the Hyottoko gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.00,0:19:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But when did it get out?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.67,0:19:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.39,0:19:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, Mr. Hyaku and Dororo \Nare back to being friends again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.60,0:19:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's get on with the wedding...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.65,0:19:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, if everyone was speaking \Nin opposites because of the ghoul...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.11,0:20:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.70,0:20:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Dororo and Mr. Hyaku were too, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.08,0:20:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, it's not Mr. Hyaku's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.63,0:20:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.76,0:20:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okowa, you don't need to marry him anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.01,0:20:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell you \Nhow I felt all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.43,0:20:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I promise to make you happier \Nthan grouchy face here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.60,0:20:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you marry me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.78,0:20:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.95,0:20:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Okowa looks happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.08,0:20:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, \NPapa's the best swordmaker in the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.13,0:21:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The swords are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.27,0:21:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You like them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.44,0:21:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro looks so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.94,0:21:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I look happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.74,0:21:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been through harsh fates \Nno normal human could even imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.75,0:21:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not over for them yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.50,0:21:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no place for you by his side \Nto begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.42,0:21:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about that. Dealing with \Nghouls like that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.01,0:21:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-Don't rub your head on people anymore. \N-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.68,0:21:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it'll go pear-shaped!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.31,0:21:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Pear...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.19,0:21:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll explain later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.73,0:22:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get going then, bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.23,0:22:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You go with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.24,0:22:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Duh. I'm the only one \Nwho can handle this journey with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.37,0:22:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We look happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.74,0:22:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Born into this world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.41,0:22:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no salvation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.00,0:22:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The distorted shape of the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.37,0:23:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet it beats courageously
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.92,0:23:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no turning back
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.92,0:23:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even from the path of evil
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.97,0:23:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Witnessing the withering seasons
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.39,0:23:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We search for the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.47,0:23:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In our ugliness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.31,0:23:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't even recognize the pain
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.94,0:23:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As we peel back the skin
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.86,0:23:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We are forever tormented by our stupidity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.49,0:23:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the dawn never comes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.99,0:23:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the painful night
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.12,0:23:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You who distrusts nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.42,0:23:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be able to love  \N this accursed world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.30,0:23:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we carry the world  \N on our shoulders
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.72,0:23:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to take it back
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.01,0:24:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"Amanojaku"
